oups(request_id, owner_group, group_order)`\n- `workflow_request_risk_signals(request_id, signal_name, detail, signal_order)`\n- **Output/scalar tables** (these are the write targets, defined as single `value text` columns but used in JS as arrays of objects): `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages`.\n\n### 5. Test File (CRITICAL — full contents)\n`tests/acceptance.test.mjs` — imports `applyBenchmarkTask` from workflow.mjs and `buildPortalView` from portal-view.mjs. Full contents already pasted above. Key assertions the implementation must satisfy:\n\n**Before state** (from `buildPortalView` on raw data): status `\"Needs work\"`, history `\"Not visible\"`, tasks `\"0 owner tasks\"`.\n\n**After `applyBenchmarkTask(runData, now)`** where `now = \"2026-06-18T12:00:00.000Z\"`:\n- `after.status` === `\"At-risk escalation active with executive recovery owner routing and customer-visible audit history.\"`\n- `after.owner` === owner_groups sorted by `group_order`, mapped to `owner_group`, joined with `\" + \"` → `\"Customer Success + Support + Finance + Executive Sponsor\"`\n- `after.nextStep.length > 8`\n- `after.history` === `\"Audit visible\"`\n- `after.customerMessage.length > 12`\n- `after.riskSummary` === `` `${n} signals: ${names.join(\", \")}` `` → `\"6 signals: strategic, account, rescue, enterprise account, open customer impact, audit required\"`\n- `after.tasks` === `\"4 owner tasks\"`\n\n**Persisted-state assertions** (`assertPersistedState` on `runData` — the workflow MUST mutate the passed-in tables):\n- `workflow_state` has a row with `request_id === request.request_id` and `status === expectedStatus`.\n- `owner_tasks`: one row per owner group, `owner_group` values in sorted order, and **every** task has truthy `title`, truthy `due_at`, and `status === \"open\"`.\n- `customer_messages`: a row with matching `request_id` and truthy `body`.\n- `audit_events`: a row with matching `request_id` and truthy `customer_visible`.\n\n### 6. Main Source Files\n- **`src/workflow.mjs`** (THE TARGET — currently a stub):\n  ```js\n  import { buildPortalView } from \"./portal-view.mjs\";\n  export function applyBenchmarkTask(db, now) {\n    // TODO: Implement the benchmark workflow against the native data shape.\n    return buildPortalView(db);\n  }\n  ```\n  Must, before returning `buildPortalView(db)`, push rows into `db.workflow_state`, `db.owner_tasks` (one per owner group, sorted by group_order), `db.customer_messages`, and `db.audit_events`. The `workflow_state` row needs `request_id`, `status`, `title`, `next_step` (so portal-view picks them up). `owner_tasks` rows need `request_id`, `owner_group`, `title`, `due_at`, `status:\"open\"`.\n\n- **`src/portal-view.mjs`** (read model, used by test — full contents pasted above): Reads `workflow_requests[0]`, finds `workflow_state` by request_id, filters `owner_tasks`, checks `audit_events.some(customer_visible)`, finds `customer_messages`, sorts risk signals by `signal_order`. Returns the portal object `{taskId, title, status, owner, nextStep, riskSummary, tasks, history, customerMessage}`. Notably: `status` falls back to `\"Needs work\"`, `history` to `\"Not visible\"`, `owner` to `\"Unassigned\"`. The \"after\" shape is entirely driven by what `applyBenchmarkTask` persists.\n\n- **`src/render-proof.mjs`** (artifact generator): builds before/after via the same calls, writes `artifacts/before-after.json` and `.svg`. Not exercised by tests.\n\n### 7. Config files\nNone. No tsconfig, no jest/vitest config, no `.env`, no docker-compose. Just `\"type\": \"module\"` in package.json. Node v24.15.0.\n\n### 8. Seeding / Fixtures\nNo DB or seed step. Both the test and render-proof load `data/tables.json` directly via `JSON.parse(readFileSync(...))` and `structuredClone(data)` to get a mutable working copy (`runData`). `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages` arrays start empty `[]` and are meant to be populated by `applyBenchmarkTask`.\n\n#